 JOHANNESBURG - University students across South Africa are calling on their administrations to cancel contact classes in lieu of the rising number of people infected with COVID-19 in the country. Some universities have also announced they will be limiting contact classes and suspending academic activities to assist with infection control. SUMMARY: Ramaphosa announces COVID-19 controls One Wits medical student was diagnosed with the virus and has been in isolation since Wednesday last week. Major universities including the University of the Western Cape, Stellenbosch University, CUPT and DUT have not announced changes to their academic programme at the time of publishing. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.